00:00:01.310 --> 00:00:04.480
This video is about the
third of the great trio

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:07.030
of partial
differential equations.

00:00:07.030 --> 00:00:09.130
Laplace's equation
was number one.

00:00:09.130 --> 00:00:11.990
That's called an
elliptic equation.

00:00:11.990 --> 00:00:14.310
The heat equation
was number two.

00:00:14.310 --> 00:00:17.040
That's called a
parabolic equation.

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:19.340
Now we reach the wave equation.

00:00:19.340 --> 00:00:23.270
That's number three, and it's
called a hyperbolic equation.

00:00:23.270 --> 00:00:26.760
So somehow the three
equations remind us

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:30.000
of ellipses, parabolas,
and hyperbolas.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.560
They have different
types of solutions.

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:36.960
Laplace's equation, you
solve it inside a circle

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:39.860
or inside some closed region.

00:00:39.860 --> 00:00:43.440
The heat equation and
the wave equation, time

00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:47.920
enters, and you're
going forward in time.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.170
The heat equation is first
order in time, du dt.

00:00:52.170 --> 00:00:56.620
And the wave equation, the
full-scale wave equation,

00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:58.570
is second order in time.

00:00:58.570 --> 00:01:02.140
That stands for the second
derivative, d second u

00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:03.480
dt squared.

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:06.360
And it matches the
second derivative

00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:11.360
in space with a velocity
coefficient c squared.

00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:16.710
I'm in one-dimensional space.

00:01:16.710 --> 00:01:19.810
If I were in three
dimensions, where we really

00:01:19.810 --> 00:01:24.050
have sound waves and light
waves and all the most important

00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:29.150
things in life, then there
would be a uxx and a uyy

00:01:29.150 --> 00:01:35.010
and a uzz, second derivatives
in all the space directions.

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:37.670
But that's good enough to do 1D.

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:40.220
So what are the
differences, first of all,

00:01:40.220 --> 00:01:43.220
